FBIS3-46771 "dreas003_m_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-003 Document Type:Daily Report 5 Jan 1994 Thailand Phaithun To Succeed Chawalit as Labor Minister BK0501004794 Bangkok BANGKOK POST in English 5 Jan 94 p 1 BK0501004794 Bangkok BANGKOK POST Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Deputy labour and Social Welfare Minister Phaithun Kaeothong yesterday was handpicked by New Aspiration Party [NAP] leader Chawalit Yongchaiyut to succeed him as minister. Mr Phaithun told a press conference that he would continue another 100-day operation plan, earlier proposed by Gen Chawalit, to speed up administration at the ministry. Gen Chawalit yesterday asked permission from the party executive committee to appoint Mr Phaithun to succeed him at the Labour and Social Welfare Ministry. He also received permission to appoint or transfer party ministers before informing the executive committee. "In any case, I can talk to the Premier to transfer NAP ministers without the advance permission of the executive committee," said the NAP leader. Gen Chawalit also told the press conference that the NAP would cooperate with other coalition parties to improve the efficiency of the government.
